<br>
1. Nobody is in the zone and it is at full pop, so you die almost instantly to roamers.<br>
2. Nodody is in the zone but it has been recently cleared. Feel free to wander around and check the place out.<br>
3. Somebody is in the zone and is now very angry at you because you could very easily kill their raid by aggroing the wrong thing in the wrong place.<br>
<br>
Do not just arbitrarily zone into Fear, please.<br>
<br>
Hate and Sky you cannot get to unless a wizard takes you. Mischief you're not going to unless you're uber. I don't know the details on Growth. You don't need a wizard, but you might need a key, I haven't been there yet myself.<br>
<br>
SOP to get into a plane is to know somebody else who's going to the plane. Have a friend in a plane-capable guild and let him know that you'd like to tag along next time. As a magician you are not a critical class, so it is important to have friends. (Clerics, enchanters, rogues, and monks have no trouble at all getting into plane raids.)<br>
<br>
Planes work differently from other zones. You can't just walk in, sit down, and camp some spawns. Plane mobs are very tough. Any one mob is fully capable of wiping out a group of 30 people, unless people are alert and skilled. Hate and Fear are jam packed with roamers, such that breaking into the zone and clearing a spot to sit down is a nightmarish event requiring 3 well balanced groups or more. Hate and Fear have no zone to run to. Once you're in the only way out is to be ported or to gate. <br>
<br>
If you're going to Sky, expect to spend a lot of money and walk away with nothing. If you're going to Hate, expect to be told &quot;no pets allowed.&quot; If you're going to Fear, expect to not get any loot, except maybe some cryosilk. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 53rd Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubindatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bindatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(3/27/01 9:00:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane raids/groups</span><hr size=1>    Actually it would be very sad if ONE single mob wiped out 30 people hehe.  Even non skilled could do one.  The thing is theres never just one usually =P,  till u get situated (flawless break ins i love hehe).  Just if u get a rough break in, u r gonna be waiting for rez.<br>
   PoG u do NOT need a key.  just click on da mushroom tree and u r in =P.  Just know that this zone isnt like other planes.  It has faction based mobs.  Also contains mobs that have a TON of hp.  PoG is kinda dead now since they upgraded kael and skyshrine armor.  <br>
   Well main thing is,  if u want to do planes u probably will have to join another guild that does do planes. Thats really the only thing i see that u r able to do to get yer planes armor.  <br>
   IF u want to stay in yer guild that does not do planes, well....id advise just trying to get gems and the armor in velious and do the thurgadin quests.  Same stats as PoG armor.  (skyshrine and kael quests are better stats but also harder to obtain).<br>
   Planes are not a place to just walk into and shout for groups.  That isnt the way they work.  Planes are scheduled events by guilds not just exp/farming for normal play hehe. So dont ever do that hehe.  Cause if yer guild cant do it u might have just lost yer corpse and all yer items.<br>
   <br>
<br>
